{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"f5d9d75b-045c-4578-a906-d9d0ae0e714a","content":"Here's what needs to change:\n\n1. **Remove** the old assembly reference to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Add** the `MSTest` v3 NuGet package (single meta-package replaces framework + adapter)\n3. **Update** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` to a current version\n\nYour test code (`[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, `Assert.*`, `[Timeout]`) is fully compatible — no C# changes needed.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01K84k1dZFef6D95jFpwmFuB","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Upgrading to MSTest v3"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_011krPeWLq75MpK5M3dyyYhG","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-36c873263daa4f44bc73a08b909f2c11/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Reference Include=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework\" />\n  </ItemGroup>\n\n  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.5.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.8.3\" />\n    <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk\" Version=\"17.13.0\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-36c873263daa4f44bc73a08b909f2c11/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"c89a3d68-4df7-48b9-93a1-c0d5eba48765","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .NET Framework test project that uses the old MSTest via assembly reference (`Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`). They want to upgrade to MSTest v3.\n\nHere's what needs to change:\n\n1. **Remove the old assembly reference** to `Microsoft.VisualStudio.QualityTools.UnitTestFramework`\n2. **Add the MSTest v3 NuGet package** — MSTest v3 ships as a single meta-package `MSTest` (version 3.x). This replaces both `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter`.\n\n\n3. **Update the target framework if needed** — MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2 and above, so most projects should be compatible without changes. The `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` package can stay or be updated, though it's not strictly required with MSTest v3 since the framework includes its own test runner.\n\nThe actual test code should work as-is — attributes like `[TestClass]`, `[TestMethod]`, assertions, and timeouts are all still supported in v3, and the `Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestTools.UnitTesting` namespace remains unchanged.","outputTokens":946,"requestId":"A03E:262AAE:1C4F15B:2033995:69FE9E05"},"id":"8a2e4096-621f-4af1-b344-9c8bfd7eb929","timestamp":"2026-05-09T02:38:14.176Z","parentId":"2868f8b2-0f92-4ca8-8f5d-145d35bb182d"}
